{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:28:58.630939+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I now have all the information needed. Here's the answer:\n\n---\n\n## `vidpack` Encoding Profiles\n\nThe `vidpack` command ships with **three profiles** defined in the checked-in `profiles.toml`:\n\n| Profile | Container | Video Codec | Audio Codec | Notes |\n|---------|-----------|-------------|-------------|-------|\n| **`web`** | **MP4** | **libx264** | **aac** | 720p, target bitrate 2 Mbps |\n| **`archive`** | **MKV** | **libx265** | **flac** | Source resolution, CRF 18 |\n| **`gif`** | **GIF** | *(palette-based)* | *(none)* | 480p wide, 12 fps |\n\n### Details\n\n- **`web`** — Produces an **MP4** container with **H.264 (libx264)** video and **AAC** audio. Scales to 1280×720 with a 2 Mbps target bitrate.\n\n- **`archive`** — Produces a **Matroska (MKV)** container with **H.265 (libx265)** video and **FLAC** (lossless) audio. Keeps the source resolution and uses CRF 18 for high quality.\n\n- **`gif`** — Produces an animated **GIF** file (no separate audio codec). Uses single-pass palette generation at 480p wide and 12 fps.\n\nThe README also mentions that the maintained wheel includes a fourth **`production`** profile (MP4 container, libx265 video, Opus audio, 1080p) used by the upstream packaging pipeline, but that profile is **not** present in the checked-in `profiles.toml` — it is only bundled in the published wheel. So from the source tree, users have three profiles to select from.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 437, "prompt_tokens": 6653, "total_tokens": 7090, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 15, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 5184, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {